hardAttenborough07TIFF.jpg|75px]] | [[Richard Attenborough|The Lord Attenborough]] | [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] | [[Life peer]] | [[BAFTA|BAFTAs]] and [[Academy Award|Academy Awards]] Actor, producer, director and entrepreneur |- | [[Image:Blank.svg|75px]] | [[John Attlee, 3rd Earl Attlee|The Earl Attlee]] | [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] | [[List of excepted hereditary peers under the House of Lords Act 1999|Excepted hereditary peer]] | [[Lord-in-Waiting|Government whip]] |- | [[Image:Lord-Avebury-2006.jpg|75px]] | [[Eric Lubbock, 4th Baron Avebury|The Lord Avebury]] | [[Liberal Democrats|Liberal Democrat]] | [[List of excepted hereditary peers under the House of Lords Act 1999|Excepted hereditary peer]] | |- | [[Image:William Bach, Baron Bach Pentagon 011026-D-9880W-096.jpg|75px]] | [[William Bach, Baron Bach|The Lord Bach]] | [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] | [[Life peer]] | Former parliamentary under-secretary of state in several departments and former [[Minister of State for Defence Procurement]] |- | [[Image:Blank.svg|75px]] | [[Kenneth Baker, Baron Baker of Dorking|The Lord Baker of Dorking]] | [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] | [[Life peer]] | Former [[Home Secretary]], former [[Secretary of State for Education and Science]] and former [[Secretary of State for the Environment|of the Environment]] |- | [[Image:Blank.svg|75px]] | [[Joan Bakewell|The Baroness Bakewell]] | [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] | [[Life peer]] | Writer and broadcaster |- | [[Image:Blank.svg|75px]] | [[Edward Baldwin, 4th Earl Baldwin of Bewdley|The Earl Baldwin of Bewdley]] | [[Crossbencher|Crossbench]] | [[List of excepted hereditary peers under the House of Lords Act 1999|Excepted hereditary peer]] | |- | [[Image:Blank.svg|75px]] | [[Edward Haughey, Baron Ballyedmond|The Lord Ballyedmond]] | [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] | [[Life peer]] | Also a Senator in the Irish [[Seanad Ãireann|Seanad]] |- | [[Image:Blank.svg|75px]] | [[Robert Lindsay, 29th Earl of Craw