===Peers on leave of absence=== The following peers were granted a [[House_of_Lords#Leave_of_absence|Leave of Absence]] for the remainder of the session or the current parliament<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.parliament.uk/about/faqs/house-of-lords-faqs/lords-leave-of-absence/ |title=House of Lords, Official Website - Members of the House of Lords granted leave of absence |accessdate=7 October 2010}}</ref> under section 23 of the Standing Orders of the House of Lords.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld/ldstords/147/14702.htm#a28 |title=Standing Orders of the House of Lords |accessdate=7 October 2010}}</ref> Members marked as '''Retired''' have elected to participate in the new retirement scheme, under which peers have the option to signal their intention to permanently retire and have their service recognised in the House and marked informally outside the House.<ref>"[http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld201012/ldselect/ldprohse/151/15104.htm Procedure Committee, 5th Report: Members Leaving the House]".</ref><ref>[http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld201011/ldhansrd/text/110627-0001.htm#11062710000466 House of Lords Debates 27 June 2011 c. 1519â31].</ref><!-- REPLACE THESE TWO SOURCES WHEN THE THE NEW COMPANION TO THE STANDING ORDERS COMES OUT -->
