==Peers disqualified== ===Members of the European Parliament=== [[Image:Sarah Ludford MEP at Bournemouth.jpg|right|140px|thumb|The Baroness Ludford]] Per sections 3 and 4 of the European Parliament (House of Lords Disqualification) Regulations 2008, peers are disqualified from sitting and voting in the House of Lords while serving as a [[Member of the European Parliament]].<ref>[http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2008/1647/contents/made The European Parliament (House of Lords Disqualification) Regulations 2008] S.I. 2008/1647, s 3â4.</ref> The folllowing peer is currently subject to this regulation:
*[[Sarah Ludford, Baroness Ludford|Baroness Ludford]], [[Liberal Democrats|Liberal Democrat]] MEP for [[London (European Parliament constituency)|London]]
===Senior judges=== [[Image:Igor Judge 2007.jpg|right|140px|thumb|The Baron Judge]] Per section 137 (3) of the [[Constitutional Reform Act 2005]], holders of certain judicial offices who are peers are disqualified from sitting and voting in the House of Lords while in office.<ref>[http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2005/4/section/137#section-137-3 Constitutional Reform Act 2005, Section 137 (3)] at legislation.gov.uk</ref> The following peers are currently subject to this provison:
;Supreme Court *[[Nicholas Phillips, Baron Phillips of Worth Matravers|The Lord Phillips of Worth Matravers]], [[President of the Supreme Court of the United Kingdom]] *[[David Hope, Baron Hope of Craighead|The Lord Hope of Craighead]], [[Deputy President of the Supreme Court of the United Kingdom]] *[[Simon Brown, Baron Brown of Eaton-under-Heywood|The Lord Brown of Eaton-under-Heywood]], [[Justice of the Supreme Court of the United Kingdom]] *[[Anthony Clarke, Baron Clarke of Stone-cum-Ebony|The Lord Clarke of Stone-cum-Ebony]], [[Justice of the Supreme Court of the United Kingdom]] *[[Lawrence Collins, Baron Collins of Mapesbury|The Lord Collins of Mapesbury]], [[Justice of the Supreme Court of the United Kingdom]] *[[Brenda Hale, Baroness Hale of Richmond|The Baroness Hale of Richmond]], [[Justice of the Supreme Court of the United Kingdom]] *[[Brian Kerr, Baron Kerr of Tonaghmore|The Lord Kerr of Tonaghmore]], [[Justice of the Supreme Court of the United Kingdom]] *[[Jonathan Mance, Baron Mance|The Lord Mance]], [[Justice of the Supreme Court of the United Kingdom]] *[[Robert Walker, Baron Walker of Gestingthorpe|The Lord Walker of Gestingthorpe]], [[Justice of the Supreme Court of the United Kingdom]]
;Court of Session *[[Lynda Clark, Baroness Clark of Calton|The Baroness Clark of Calton]], Judge of the [[Court of Session]] *[[Andrew Hardie, Baron Hardie|The Lord Hardie]], Judge of the [[Court of Session]] *[[Donald Mackay, Baron Mackay of Drumadoon|The Lord Mackay of Drumadoon]], Judge of the [[Court of Session]]
;Others *[[Igor Judge, Baron Judge|The Lord Judge]], [[Lord Chief Justice of England and Wales]] *[[David Neuberger, Baron Neuberger of Abbotsbury|The Lord Neuberger of Abbotsbury]], [[Master of the Rolls]]
===Permanently disqualified=== [[Image:Norman Foster dresden 061110.jpg|right|140px|thumb|The Baron Foster of Thames Bank]] Under section 41 of the Constitutional Reform and Governance Act 2010, peers must be [[Taxation in the United Kingdom#Residence and domicile|domiciled in the United Kingdom for tax purposes]]. Section 42 allowed peers who did not wish to comply with the provision to choose within three months of the act coming into force to become permanently disqualified from being members of the House.<ref>[http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2010/25//section/42 Constitutional Reform and Governance Act 2010 s 42].</ref>The following peers made that election and are still living:
*[[Raj Bagri, Baron Bagri|Lord Bagri]], [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] *[[Lydia Dunn, Baroness Dunn|Baroness Dunn]], [[Crossbencher|Crossbench]] * [[Norman Foster, Baron Foster of Thames Bank|Lord Foster of Thames Bank]], [[Crossbencher|Crossbench]] *[[Irvine Laidlaw, Baron Laidlaw|Lord Laidlaw]], [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] * [[Alistair McAlpine, Baron McAlpine of West Green|Lord McAlpine of West Green]], [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]]
